N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 10 ยง 11.131 - Entry level qualifications

State Regulations
A local public health nutritionist must possess a baccalaureate degree, with major studies in food and nutrition, from a regionally accredited or New York State-registered college or university, and be registered as a dietician by the American Dietetic Association. Notes
